WEBVTT

00:22.605 --> 00:25.442
Can you hear the drums, Fernando?

00:27.402 --> 00:31.823
I remember long ago
Another starry night like this

00:34.325 --> 00:35.326
In the fire…

00:37.662 --> 00:39.748
Dadgum it!

00:45.086 --> 00:46.337
No!

00:49.674 --> 00:51.009
Help! Help!

00:51.092 --> 00:52.719
Mom!

00:52.802 --> 00:54.471
Mom! Dad!

01:04.230 --> 01:05.231
Mom!

01:06.608 --> 01:08.568
Mom! Mom!

01:09.819 --> 01:11.654
-Holly?
-Mom! Mom!

01:11.738 --> 01:14.449
-Mom, the monster!
-Baby, what are you doing? What's wrong?

01:14.532 --> 01:18.745
-Mom, there's a monster in there.
-Holly, slow down. I can't understand you!

01:18.828 --> 01:20.872
-Mom, there's a monster. The mon--
-Holly.

01:21.581 --> 01:24.042
Whatever you saw, baby,
it was just a nightmare.

01:24.125 --> 01:26.795
-No, Mom! Mom!
-Baby, it's just a nightmare!

01:26.878 --> 01:29.089
I saw it. Please trust me, Mom.

01:29.923 --> 01:33.676
Please, Mom, please.
You gotta believe me. Please.

01:50.110 --> 01:51.611
What the heck?

02:05.208 --> 02:06.626
What's your location? Over.

02:07.418 --> 02:08.753
Pickett, five minutes away.

02:08.837 --> 02:11.005
You're way ahead of us.
Radio as soon as you're there!

02:11.089 --> 02:12.006
I will.

02:12.090 --> 02:13.925
And Nancy, be careful.

02:14.008 --> 02:14.926
Hold on.

02:22.183 --> 02:25.186
There was something
In the air that night

02:27.188 --> 02:29.858
The stars were bright, Fernando

02:31.067 --> 02:34.154
They were shining there for you and me

02:34.237 --> 02:38.449
For liberty, Fernando

02:38.533 --> 02:42.412
Though we never thought
That we could lose

02:42.495 --> 02:43.997
There's no regret

02:46.124 --> 02:48.585
If I had to do the same again

02:54.674 --> 02:57.302
There was something
In the air that night

02:59.304 --> 03:01.055
The stars were bright, Fernando

03:10.190 --> 03:11.024
Karen!

03:18.323 --> 03:20.200
Heavens to Betsy.

03:21.117 --> 03:22.118
Karen!

03:24.913 --> 03:26.206
Everything all right?

03:29.459 --> 03:30.460
Holly?

03:38.801 --> 03:39.802
Holly!

03:41.012 --> 03:42.555
Holy smokes.

03:46.309 --> 03:49.520
Oh God. Hey. Stay back. Stay back!

03:49.604 --> 03:50.647
Back!

04:13.002 --> 04:13.878
Go! Go!

04:18.132 --> 04:19.008
Mom!

04:23.263 --> 04:24.597
Oh, God!

04:24.681 --> 04:25.932
Holly, get back!

04:35.316 --> 04:40.530
Stay away from my daughter!

04:41.948 --> 04:42.949
Mom, no!

04:56.004 --> 04:57.297
It's inside.

04:57.380 --> 04:59.257
I see it. Get ready.

05:14.314 --> 05:17.233
Nancy, what's going on?
Talk to me! What's happening?

05:18.484 --> 05:19.444
Nancy!

05:23.865 --> 05:28.494
Stay away from my daughter!

06:06.240 --> 06:07.158
Mom!

06:11.579 --> 06:14.999
Don't try to talk, okay?
Just stay calm, okay?

06:15.083 --> 06:17.543
You're gonna be fine.
It's gonna be fine, okay?

06:18.127 --> 06:19.087
You're gonna be fine.

06:19.170 --> 06:20.088
Holly.

06:40.066 --> 06:42.527
Go. Go, go, go, go! Go!

06:45.488 --> 06:49.492
You're gonna be okay, Mom.
I'm right here. Just stay with me. Okay?

06:49.575 --> 06:51.953
Can you do that?
Can you please stay with me?

06:52.036 --> 06:53.788
I promise
I won't let anything happen to you.

06:53.871 --> 06:56.833
I'm gonna get you help.
I just need you to hold on, okay?

06:56.916 --> 06:58.126
Just hold on.

08:08.696 --> 08:09.989
Vitals. Talk to me.

08:10.072 --> 08:11.699
Female, 46 years old.

08:11.782 --> 08:14.785
-Heart rate 120. BP 103/67.
-Got a male, late forties.

08:14.869 --> 08:16.496
Multiple blunt impact. Weak abdominal…

08:16.579 --> 08:18.331
Pulse is thready and weak.

08:18.414 --> 08:21.542
Lacerations to the right anterior chest
and penetrating neck trauma.

08:21.626 --> 08:23.044
We're right here. You're okay.

08:23.628 --> 08:25.421
I'm sorry. You have to wait outside.

08:25.505 --> 08:28.549
-Can't we stay with them?
-We have to let the doctors do their job.

08:28.633 --> 08:31.719
We'll update you
as soon as we know something, okay? Okay?

08:31.802 --> 08:33.179
I can't see a damn thing.

08:33.679 --> 08:35.431
Cross-match, get to the bag.

08:35.515 --> 08:36.766
Where’s my X-ray cart?

08:36.849 --> 08:39.227
-Maybe four broken ribs.
-Stand by to intubate.

09:38.661 --> 09:40.079
This is our fault.

09:42.290 --> 09:43.874
This is all our fault.

09:47.086 --> 09:48.629
We got there as fast as we could.

09:49.338 --> 09:51.632
I'm not talking about tonight.

09:51.716 --> 09:57.430
We could have acted yesterday,
last week, last fall.

09:57.513 --> 09:59.599
We could've tried
to get them out of Hawkins,

09:59.682 --> 10:02.518
or… or at least told them the truth.

10:02.602 --> 10:05.730
We could have done something, anything.

10:05.813 --> 10:08.691
We couldn't have known
any of this would happen.

10:08.774 --> 10:10.109
Do you really believe that?

10:10.901 --> 10:13.529
After all this time, it comes for Holly?

10:13.613 --> 10:15.906
Holly, who has nothing to do
with any of this.

10:15.990 --> 10:17.700
It makes no goddamn sense.

10:17.783 --> 10:20.620
It makes perfect goddamn sense.

10:20.703 --> 10:22.371
Vecna told me this would happen.

10:22.455 --> 10:23.914
He showed me.

10:23.998 --> 10:25.416
And not just the four gates.

10:25.499 --> 10:27.168
Holly, Mom, Dad dead.

10:27.877 --> 10:30.880
And we just…
we just chose not to believe him.

10:31.672 --> 10:34.967
But now it's all coming true.
Like, don't you get it, Mike?

10:35.635 --> 10:39.764
Vecna's come back
to realize his vision, to punish us.

10:39.847 --> 10:42.016
He did it with Fred and Chrissy and Max,

10:42.099 --> 10:43.267
and now it's our turn.

10:43.351 --> 10:44.727
And he's not gonna stop.

10:44.810 --> 10:48.648
He's not gonna stop until we're drained
of every last ounce of suffering.

10:49.482 --> 10:52.234
I'm not so sure this was about punishment.

10:53.277 --> 10:55.363
Vecna doesn't leave things unfinished.

10:55.446 --> 10:57.198
He doesn't hold back.

10:57.281 --> 11:01.452
Because if this was really about
making you guys suffer,

11:01.535 --> 11:03.204
why leave your parents alive?

11:03.287 --> 11:05.289
Why take Holly into the Upside Down

11:05.373 --> 11:07.124
and not leave her body here
for you to find?

11:07.208 --> 11:08.834
Why not come here himself?

11:08.918 --> 11:10.836
Why send one of his… his pets?

11:10.920 --> 11:12.838
What are you saying? It's not Vecna?

11:13.673 --> 11:16.175
What I'm saying is I don't know,

11:16.258 --> 11:17.510
and neither do you.

11:17.593 --> 11:19.637
There are just too many questions
right now.

11:19.720 --> 11:23.265
I… I just know I'm having serious déjà vu,

11:23.349 --> 11:25.685
because this is
exactly what happened to Will

11:25.768 --> 11:27.895
at almost exactly the same time.

11:32.316 --> 11:34.694
You know what date it is, right?

11:35.569 --> 11:36.904
November 3rd.

11:36.987 --> 11:38.823
Will was taken on the 6th.

11:39.490 --> 11:41.367
We are less than three days away.

11:42.743 --> 11:45.955
Three days away
from the day that changed everything.

11:47.873 --> 11:49.834
I don't know about you guys, but…

11:52.461 --> 11:54.255
…I don't believe in coincidences.

11:56.799 --> 11:57.758
Not anymore.

11:59.760 --> 12:01.137
But we got Will back.

12:01.220 --> 12:03.514
And we're going to get Holly back,
'cause she's not alone.

12:03.597 --> 12:05.266
Eleven's in there with her.

12:05.349 --> 12:07.268
And if anybody can save your sister--

12:07.351 --> 12:08.602
It's El.

12:09.937 --> 12:10.855
It's El.

12:16.694 --> 12:18.529
Stay indoors!

12:18.612 --> 12:20.614
Stay inside!

12:36.380 --> 12:38.215
The daughter found her mother here.

12:38.299 --> 12:41.886
We believe Mrs. Wheeler was trying
to escape when she was attacked.

12:42.928 --> 12:45.014
And no one saw this intruder?

12:45.097 --> 12:47.975
No. By the time she got home,
the intruder was gone,

12:48.058 --> 12:49.310
along with her sister.

12:53.773 --> 12:55.566
The daughter, she arrive alone?

12:55.649 --> 12:57.276
That's what she told us, sir.

13:15.419 --> 13:17.254
I want you to pull up
all video surveillance

13:17.338 --> 13:19.673
within a two-mile radius of this house.

13:20.341 --> 13:22.468
-You think it could be her, sir?
-Now.

13:38.484 --> 13:41.821
Holly! Holly!

13:43.322 --> 13:44.406
Holly!

14:34.164 --> 14:35.082
Hop.

14:36.208 --> 14:37.251
Hop!

14:38.294 --> 14:39.169
Hop?

14:39.253 --> 14:41.589
I'm sorry. Are you okay?

14:41.672 --> 14:42.840
El.

14:44.049 --> 14:45.384
How are you here?

14:53.183 --> 14:54.768
Wait. Wait.

14:56.228 --> 14:57.938
Wait. You gotta…

14:58.022 --> 15:01.358
You gotta get out of here. It's not safe.

15:01.442 --> 15:03.235
-There's--
-A Demogorgon.

15:03.319 --> 15:04.904
I know. It's bleeding.

15:06.071 --> 15:07.698
She must have hurt it.

15:07.781 --> 15:08.866
What? Who?

15:09.658 --> 15:11.410
Karen. With her wine.

15:12.119 --> 15:13.120
What?

15:14.038 --> 15:17.666
When I search for Holly,
I can't find her, but she must be close.

15:17.750 --> 15:19.919
-Holly?
-We just need to find the blood.

15:20.002 --> 15:22.212
Holly Wheeler? What are you…

15:23.005 --> 15:25.591
El, wait! Goddamn it!

15:32.056 --> 15:33.057
Whoa.

15:33.682 --> 15:36.435
It's like everything went kablooey
all at once.

15:41.982 --> 15:44.735
Has this kind of thing happened
with his visions before?

15:44.818 --> 15:47.821
Where the lights go kooky
and electronics short-circuit?

15:47.905 --> 15:49.323
No.

15:49.406 --> 15:51.909
So this is just, like,
a fun, new development.

15:52.701 --> 15:54.787
Aren't there any backup fuses
or something?

15:54.870 --> 15:58.248
Yeah, in storage, I think so.
I mean, I hope so, right?

16:00.376 --> 16:03.170
Oh! Uh… You'd like me to go get them?

16:03.253 --> 16:04.463
-Yeah.
-Right.

16:04.546 --> 16:07.675
Uh, of course. I am totally on it.

16:07.758 --> 16:09.426
I… I'll be right back.

16:15.516 --> 16:17.893
I know it's hard to talk about,

16:17.977 --> 16:21.647
but these… these visions,

16:22.690 --> 16:23.816
were they like before?

16:23.899 --> 16:26.652
Like when you had your now memories?

16:31.699 --> 16:34.702
Only more intense.

16:34.785 --> 16:38.956
It's like I was there. I was right there.

16:41.083 --> 16:45.254
It's… It's like I was the Demogorgon.

16:47.297 --> 16:53.762
I was seeing what it was seeing
and thinking what it was thinking.

16:54.555 --> 16:58.100
Do you have any idea
why it would go after the Wheelers,

16:58.183 --> 16:59.393
take Holly?

16:59.476 --> 17:01.770
I don't… I'm not sure. It's…

17:02.563 --> 17:08.652
It's so hard to remember everything.
It's… It's almost like a dream.

17:08.736 --> 17:11.363
This doesn't make any sense. I…

17:11.447 --> 17:17.036
I… I must have somehow
tapped back into the hive mind.

17:17.119 --> 17:18.746
But we severed the connection.

17:20.622 --> 17:25.419
I don't think it was ever… truly severed.

17:27.379 --> 17:31.216
Ever since he took me, it's like I… I was…

17:32.384 --> 17:34.720
permanently changed.

17:38.557 --> 17:42.436
These feelings of connection,
they come and go.

17:42.519 --> 17:45.898
But that summer, after the gate opened,

17:48.067 --> 17:49.526
I felt him again.

17:50.611 --> 17:54.740
And it went away when I was in California.

17:55.824 --> 17:57.701
But the day after I got back,

17:59.328 --> 18:00.621
the feeling returned.

18:02.748 --> 18:04.374
And now he's closer.

18:05.084 --> 18:07.461
He's closer than ever before.

18:08.462 --> 18:10.339
Maybe you're like a receiver.

18:10.422 --> 18:14.551
You know, like a radio receiver,
just a magical human version.

18:15.636 --> 18:17.930
-I… I don't follow.
-Okay.

18:20.390 --> 18:23.685
Imagine that you have an antenna
coming up from the top of your head.

18:23.769 --> 18:27.898
And Vecna, he uses
Mind Flayer particles like radio waves.

18:27.981 --> 18:31.902
When the antenna is close to the waves,
the signal comes through clear as day.

18:31.985 --> 18:33.612
But if you're too far away…

18:33.695 --> 18:34.613
Static.

18:36.365 --> 18:38.492
So maybe that's how we do it.

18:38.575 --> 18:39.868
That's how we find Holly.

18:41.245 --> 18:43.831
What, with your antenna?

18:43.914 --> 18:47.334
Earlier, I had a vision
in the woods near the school.

18:49.169 --> 18:50.754
I didn't understand it at the time,

18:50.838 --> 18:53.924
but maybe I was seeing
through the Demogorgon's eyes then too.

18:54.007 --> 18:55.342
And maybe if I go back there,

18:55.425 --> 18:57.761
I can connect back to the hive mind,
to the signal.

18:57.845 --> 18:58.679
Will.

18:58.762 --> 19:01.849
-I've spied on Vecna before.
-And he took control of you.

19:01.932 --> 19:03.809
-I know, but--
-You almost died.

19:03.892 --> 19:05.853
And Holly will too
if we don't do something.

19:05.936 --> 19:07.312
We are doing something.

19:07.396 --> 19:08.564
Replacing fuses?

19:08.647 --> 19:11.650
We've got to get the Squawk back up
so we can find Hopper.

19:11.733 --> 19:13.986
Hopper, right.
This is about your boyfriend.

19:14.069 --> 19:17.614
He's our only connection
to the Upside Down, to El.

19:17.698 --> 19:19.700
How does that get us closer to Holly?

19:19.783 --> 19:22.828
She's in there, Mom, all alone.
I know what that's like.

19:22.911 --> 19:24.663
I won't just leave her there.

19:24.746 --> 19:25.831
We're gonna get her back,

19:25.914 --> 19:28.458
but we're not gonna risk your life
while doing it.

19:33.839 --> 19:35.924
-Are you just gonna stand there?
-Right.

19:36.008 --> 19:39.178
Uh, intimate family moment. Sorry.

19:39.261 --> 19:41.180
Fuses, power. On it.

19:56.069 --> 19:57.446
How long is this gonna take?

19:57.529 --> 19:58.697
Not too long.

19:58.780 --> 20:01.658
We just gotta let this sucker charge
for a few minutes, then hopefully…

20:02.242 --> 20:03.452
vroom, vroom.

20:11.919 --> 20:13.629
Bopper, while we wait?

20:16.381 --> 20:18.759
Well, this better be quick.

20:18.842 --> 20:21.887
Our good Samaritan's turning sour.
I think she might have placed me.

20:21.970 --> 20:25.224
-Placed you?
-Stood up her sister. Multiple occasions.

20:25.307 --> 20:26.183
Great.

20:27.226 --> 20:28.518
Did you get a hold of Nance?

20:30.020 --> 20:33.732
Dad's in an induced coma,
and Mom's in surgery.

20:35.025 --> 20:37.110
They're not gonna know anything
for a couple hours.

20:38.320 --> 20:39.988
Jesus Christ, man.

20:41.907 --> 20:42.866
Yeah.

20:44.326 --> 20:46.870
You think we should go see her
at the hospital?

20:47.704 --> 20:50.207
I mean, if we can get
this hunk of junk moving.

20:50.290 --> 20:51.291
Mmm…

20:51.375 --> 20:54.086
No. No, we stick to the plan.

20:54.711 --> 20:55.921
Search Zone G1.

20:56.004 --> 20:59.716
-Find Hopper, find Eleven and find Holly.
-Right.

21:00.842 --> 21:03.762
Just… That seems complicated.

21:05.055 --> 21:07.599
Like, it might take a lot of time.

21:08.225 --> 21:09.101
Okay.

21:09.184 --> 21:11.061
You know, the hospital is on the way.

21:11.144 --> 21:13.605
We could just swing by,

21:13.689 --> 21:15.607
bring Nance, like, flowers or something.

21:15.691 --> 21:16.858
Jesus Christ.

21:16.942 --> 21:18.068
What?

21:18.151 --> 21:20.696
I just thought that,
tonight of all nights,

21:20.779 --> 21:22.489
you might just give it a rest.

21:22.572 --> 21:23.782
Give what a rest?

21:23.865 --> 21:26.702
This bullshit macho competition
for Nancy's attention.

21:26.785 --> 21:29.246
-What are you talking about?
-What am I talking about?

21:29.329 --> 21:30.998
-Yeah.
-Really?

21:31.498 --> 21:35.335
Dude, ever since I got back from Lenora,
you are constantly showing off for her.

21:35.419 --> 21:37.087
How you're better than me!

21:37.170 --> 21:38.964
Which is shitty enough on a normal day,

21:39.047 --> 21:42.301
but now her parents are fighting
for their lives, her sister is missing,

21:42.384 --> 21:44.553
and all you can think about
is giving her flowers.

21:44.636 --> 21:47.014
You selfish, chauvinistic meathead!

21:57.274 --> 21:58.358
You know what, Byers?

21:58.442 --> 22:00.277
You're totally right.

22:00.360 --> 22:03.530
Me worrying about
my good friend, my friend,

22:03.613 --> 22:05.615
that makes me the selfish one here.

22:05.699 --> 22:09.828
Or maybe, just maybe,
you're the problem, dude.

22:09.911 --> 22:11.204
Ever since you got back,

22:11.288 --> 22:13.457
you've been acting
like a paranoid pothead weirdo.

22:13.540 --> 22:17.544
And maybe if you stopped focusing on me
and started focusing on her,

22:17.627 --> 22:19.963
maybe then the two of you
would finally be happy.

22:20.047 --> 22:21.465
Because right now, the only one

22:21.548 --> 22:23.925
who's more miserable
in that relationship than you…

22:24.926 --> 22:25.761
is Nance.

22:45.280 --> 22:47.657
You've got to be shitting me.

22:56.375 --> 22:58.460
And you got there how, exactly?

22:58.543 --> 22:59.544
Get where?

22:59.628 --> 23:02.381
The Wheeler house.
Did you take the Henderson shelter?

23:02.464 --> 23:04.174
No. Nancy drove me.

23:07.302 --> 23:09.513
Nancy drove you?

23:10.764 --> 23:11.765
Yes.

23:11.848 --> 23:14.101
We don't drive ever, do we?

23:14.851 --> 23:16.603
-Do we?
-No.

23:16.686 --> 23:18.271
No, we take the tunnels,

23:18.355 --> 23:21.066
and we don't surface until it's clear,
until it's safe.

23:21.149 --> 23:22.150
I wore my hoodie.

23:22.234 --> 23:24.069
Oh, well, geez, that's great.

23:24.152 --> 23:27.155
I don't know why we've been
crawling around in the mud all this time.

23:27.239 --> 23:29.324
We should've just drove you around
in your hoodie.

23:29.408 --> 23:30.700
The tunnels are too slow.

23:30.784 --> 23:32.202
Holly was in danger.

23:32.285 --> 23:33.620
Yeah, and now so are you.

23:33.703 --> 23:36.748
If those military guys haven't already
caught you on camera, they will.

23:36.832 --> 23:37.666
And when they do,

23:37.749 --> 23:40.752
they'll be coming for you
with everything they got.

23:40.836 --> 23:43.088
Then we have to end this
before they find us.

23:43.171 --> 23:45.048
Is that what this is about, ending this?

23:45.132 --> 23:47.509
The Demogorgon can lead us to Vecna.

23:47.592 --> 23:48.468
How?

23:48.552 --> 23:52.222
When I searched for Holly,
I could not find her, just like Vecna.

23:52.806 --> 23:57.477
So maybe wherever she is, he is,
where my powers cannot reach.

23:57.561 --> 24:01.398
I'm sorry.
So your… your theory is what, exactly?

24:01.481 --> 24:05.110
It's that the Demogorgon has taken
little Holly Wheeler to Vecna

24:05.193 --> 24:07.529
as some kind of early Christmas present?

24:07.612 --> 24:12.451
What does Vecna want with Holly Wheeler?
What… How does any of this make sense?

24:12.534 --> 24:14.619
-I don't know!
-Exactly, you don't know.

24:14.703 --> 24:18.165
Because you haven't put any thought
into anything you've been doing tonight.

24:18.248 --> 24:23.295
You've been acting on impulse, on emotion,
everything I taught you not to do!

24:23.378 --> 24:25.046
Goddamn it…

24:26.089 --> 24:27.591
More blood than before.

24:28.842 --> 24:29.968
It's slowing down.

24:31.219 --> 24:32.554
We can still catch it.

24:34.306 --> 24:35.474
And not emotion.

24:37.017 --> 24:38.185
Instinct.

24:47.527 --> 24:51.156
We don't know where Hop or El are,

24:51.239 --> 24:55.285
or if they found each other or Holly,
or… or anything.

24:56.203 --> 24:58.038
We're totally in the dark up here.

25:02.042 --> 25:04.044
You don't wanna hurt me

25:05.378 --> 25:07.923
I wish I… I had better news.

25:11.384 --> 25:13.637
Hopefully my next update will be

25:14.679 --> 25:18.266
something like El and Hop saved Holly,
and killed Vecna,

25:18.350 --> 25:21.603
and everyone's back home
celebrating and everything.

25:23.605 --> 25:27.150
But if I've learned anything
over the years…

25:29.486 --> 25:31.404
it's never gonna be that easy.

25:35.575 --> 25:37.244
El's amazing.

25:39.287 --> 25:43.333
But she can't do this alone.
She's gonna need all the help she can get.

25:43.416 --> 25:46.545
She's going to need the party,
the full party.

25:47.462 --> 25:48.588
Which is why I'm here.

25:51.466 --> 25:52.592
The final battle…

25:54.219 --> 25:55.804
I feel like it started tonight.

25:58.223 --> 26:01.893
And Max, we can't win this without you.

26:02.602 --> 26:04.604
If my theory is right,
we're running out of time.

26:04.688 --> 26:08.858
So if you're planning on resurrecting
anytime soon, now… now is the time.

26:12.445 --> 26:15.574
Even a sign would be enough
to show me you're still in there.

26:19.744 --> 26:21.162
Please, Max.

26:23.206 --> 26:24.249
Please.

26:26.668 --> 26:27.752
Wake up.

26:29.546 --> 26:31.214
Just… something.

26:33.883 --> 26:35.051
I miss you.

26:36.469 --> 26:40.724
Oh, come on, angel
Come on, come on, darlin'

26:40.807 --> 26:44.853
Let's exchange the experience

27:24.309 --> 27:26.853
Okay, so, you're not gonna believe this,

27:26.936 --> 27:29.689
but she still won't give us a timeline
on seeing Mom.

27:29.773 --> 27:31.733
And… And I wasn't even asking to see Mom.

27:31.816 --> 27:34.903
I was just asking to talk to the doctor,
and she just kept saying…

27:35.403 --> 27:38.239
Mike. Mike, are you listening?

27:39.199 --> 27:41.076
Yeah. Yeah, no. Uh…

27:42.327 --> 27:44.245
I was thinking about
something Lucas said earlier,

27:44.329 --> 27:48.124
about how he doesn't believe
in coincidences anymore, and…

27:48.792 --> 27:51.002
Did Holly ever talk to you
about Mr. Whatsit?

27:51.586 --> 27:55.715
Her… imaginary friend from the book?

27:55.799 --> 27:59.719
Well, yeah, it's Mrs. Whatsit in the book.
So… So, this is her own creation.

27:59.803 --> 28:01.012
At least that's what I thought.

28:01.096 --> 28:03.056
When I went to pick her up
from school today,

28:03.139 --> 28:07.018
she said that Mr. Whatsit told her
that there were monsters in Hawkins.

28:07.102 --> 28:10.772
And he warned her that these monsters,
they were coming for her.

28:10.855 --> 28:14.067
And on the same day,
she's actually taken by a monster?

28:14.150 --> 28:17.404
I mean, as far as coincidences go,
that's a hell of a one.

28:17.487 --> 28:20.490
And your theory is… what exactly?

28:20.573 --> 28:23.535
What if Mr. Whatsit isn't a figment
of Holly's imagination?

28:25.578 --> 28:27.497
-What if he's real?
-Real?

28:28.415 --> 28:29.749
Yeah, what if?

28:29.833 --> 28:34.629
It… It doesn't make sense.
How have we never seen him?

28:34.713 --> 28:36.423
Maybe we have, and we just didn't know.

28:36.506 --> 28:38.591
-So who the hell is he?
-I don't know.

28:38.675 --> 28:41.386
-How does he know that Holly's in danger?
-I don't know.

28:41.469 --> 28:44.139
If he was so worried,
then why wouldn't he warn us or Mom

28:44.222 --> 28:45.432
or do something about it?

28:45.515 --> 28:46.933
I don't know, Nance.

28:47.016 --> 28:49.018
My theory, it has holes.

28:51.771 --> 28:55.275
You were right
about what you said earlier.

28:55.358 --> 28:59.237
We could have done more
to protect Mom and Dad and Holly, and…

29:01.072 --> 29:02.991
I don't want to have any more regrets.

29:03.074 --> 29:05.160
And maybe my theory is wrong.

29:05.243 --> 29:10.039
But if it isn't, if Mr. Whatsit is real,
then he would know things.

29:10.832 --> 29:13.460
Like why Holly was taken,
or… or maybe even--

29:13.543 --> 29:15.295
Where she was taken.

29:17.839 --> 29:21.760
And how do you propose
we go about finding out who this guy is?

29:21.843 --> 29:23.970
I was kind of hoping you'd tell me.

29:24.053 --> 29:26.973
You're the genius investigative reporter
after all.

29:27.557 --> 29:29.934
That's not fair. Appealing to my ego.

29:38.943 --> 29:42.405
Okay. I'm gonna need you
to talk to that receptionist

29:42.489 --> 29:45.867
and do your best sad,
lost boy, puppy dog thing.

29:46.618 --> 29:47.535
My what? Why?

29:47.619 --> 29:50.747
Because she hates me, and you're cute,
and we're gonna need her help

29:50.830 --> 29:54.042
if we want to get close to the one person
who knows about Mr. Whatsit,

29:54.751 --> 29:55.668
Mom.

29:58.880 --> 30:01.466
And by sheer luck,
Jessica was coming back from a party,

30:01.549 --> 30:03.551
and I charmed my way
into getting us a jump.

30:03.635 --> 30:07.889
Which brings us to you,
arriving looking like Rocky Balboa.

30:07.972 --> 30:13.353
So basically, of all the crawls,
this was, like, the one to miss.

30:13.436 --> 30:17.607
So, well done, Henderson.
Really, really, like, well done.

30:22.403 --> 30:24.113
Speechless. That's new.

30:24.197 --> 30:26.574
I'm still processing, Steve. It's a lot.

30:27.784 --> 30:28.952
Holly?

30:29.661 --> 30:30.662
Why Holly?

30:30.745 --> 30:33.832
Well, maybe Eleven could tell us,
but it's a bit difficult to contact her

30:33.915 --> 30:36.167
now that we've lost our connection
to the Upside Down.

30:36.251 --> 30:39.921
Okay. For the future, when the lights go
from really bright to really dim,

30:40.004 --> 30:42.841
it means the generator is surging
so you have to turn everything off.

30:42.924 --> 30:44.300
-Wow. Great.
-Immediately.

30:44.384 --> 30:47.428
Thank you. I'll remember that
the next time that happens.

30:47.512 --> 30:51.891
Or, maybe, and this is just a suggestion,
you could be where you're supposed to be.

30:51.975 --> 30:53.726
I was en route to the Squawk.

30:53.810 --> 30:56.563
When you fell off your bike. That's right.

30:56.646 --> 30:59.399
Remind me. What did you fall into again?
A knuckle sandwich?

30:59.482 --> 31:01.484
Hey, can you keep it down up there?

31:01.568 --> 31:04.654
I'm listening for a signal back here,
in case you forgot.

31:07.699 --> 31:10.827
Who was it?
It was Andy and his goons, wasn't it?

31:10.910 --> 31:12.871
You poked the bear one too many times.

31:12.954 --> 31:14.873
Your concern for me
is overwhelming, Steve.

31:14.956 --> 31:16.499
My concern?

31:16.583 --> 31:19.836
I have shown nothing but concern for you
since forever,

31:19.919 --> 31:22.547
and I have been repeatedly ignored,
and now look what's happened.

31:22.630 --> 31:24.007
We are totally screwed.

31:24.090 --> 31:26.050
Correction, we are screwed
because you don't know

31:26.134 --> 31:29.012
how to do the most basic thing
like prevent a power surge.

31:29.095 --> 31:32.599
-See, this right here is your problem.
-It's the easiest thing in the world.

31:32.682 --> 31:35.059
-You can't admit you were wrong.
-My mother could prevent a surge.

31:35.143 --> 31:37.353
-You can't admit it.
-Shockingly, I think your mother--

31:37.437 --> 31:39.606
Jesus Christ! Just do it for once!

31:39.689 --> 31:42.150
Just admit it, Henderson.
You're wrong! You screwed up!

31:42.233 --> 31:45.153
Hey! Can you guys shut the hell up?

31:46.237 --> 31:47.989
Jesus Christ.

31:51.868 --> 31:53.244
You two seem to be getting along.

31:53.828 --> 31:56.414
Yeah, well, in this case,
I actually like his suggestion.

31:57.582 --> 32:00.084
-I don't wanna talk to you.
-I don't wanna talk to you either.

32:00.168 --> 32:01.044
Good.

32:02.253 --> 32:03.379
Good.

32:03.463 --> 32:04.505
Good.

32:12.305 --> 32:16.601
This is Dungeon Master
to Scout Battalion. Do you copy? Over.

32:17.310 --> 32:20.313
This is Dungeon Master to Scout Battalion.

32:20.396 --> 32:22.023
Do you copy? Over.

32:26.235 --> 32:32.075
This is Dungeon Master to Scout Battalion.
Do you copy? Over.

32:34.285 --> 32:35.662
Great Scott!

32:36.788 --> 32:39.499
-How long has that light been red?
-Oh. I don't know.

32:39.582 --> 32:42.418
Shit, shit, shit!
The flux capacitor is down again.

32:42.502 --> 32:44.253
-Is that bad?
-I mean, it could be.

32:44.337 --> 32:46.422
It's fixable, but it's a two-man job.

32:47.674 --> 32:48.716
Come on.

32:50.426 --> 32:51.552
We'll be right back.

32:55.139 --> 32:56.015
Flux capacitor?

32:56.099 --> 32:58.768
Shh! I was lying, obviously.
That light is always red.

32:58.851 --> 33:00.561
Everything's totally fine, except…

33:00.645 --> 33:02.605
-Whoa.
-Except for your mom's plan.

33:02.689 --> 33:04.399
I mean, no offense to your mom,
but come on.

33:05.066 --> 33:07.652
The boys have already circled Zone G1,
like, five times.

33:07.735 --> 33:11.155
Even if they miraculously find Hopper,
where does that get us exactly?

33:11.739 --> 33:13.950
I mean, Holly is still missing.

33:14.033 --> 33:17.328
Whereas your plan is genius.

33:17.412 --> 33:18.955
-You think so?
-Totally.

33:19.038 --> 33:21.582
You got an antenna in your head, use it.

33:21.666 --> 33:24.669
The Enigma machine won the war.
Knowledge is power.

33:24.752 --> 33:27.296
-So…
-So… So, you want to…

33:27.380 --> 33:28.798
Skip school, play hooky,

33:28.881 --> 33:31.509
connect your brain into
an interdimensional monster's signal,

33:31.592 --> 33:33.511
and save little Wheeler?

33:33.594 --> 33:35.138
Yeah, kind of.

33:35.221 --> 33:38.266
I mean, your mom is gonna be raging mad,

33:38.349 --> 33:39.600
and she's probably right.

33:39.684 --> 33:41.060
It is super dangerous, but…

33:41.144 --> 33:43.146
Isn't everything we do super dangerous?

33:43.229 --> 33:46.232
Precisely. So what do you say?

33:48.109 --> 33:50.903
This is Dungeon Master to Scout Battalion.

33:50.987 --> 33:51.946
Screw it.

34:02.165 --> 34:03.875
When were these taken?

34:03.958 --> 34:05.418
Three hours ago, give or take.

34:05.501 --> 34:07.670
We've had sightings before.

34:08.171 --> 34:11.049
-Yes, but this time is different.
-Different.

34:11.674 --> 34:14.886
Don't interrupt me again
until you have her in custody.

34:14.969 --> 34:17.764
She's here, Dr. Kay.

34:19.807 --> 34:21.809
What do you mean, "here"?

34:31.444 --> 34:33.988
Hey, come on. Slow down. Hang on.

34:34.072 --> 34:36.324
I found more blood. It must be close.

34:36.407 --> 34:39.660
Oh, you goddamn stubborn punk-ass…

34:42.872 --> 34:44.248
What are you doing?

34:44.332 --> 34:45.416
We're gonna lose her.

34:45.500 --> 34:48.252
It's just a cramp. It's just old age.
Just give me a second.

34:48.336 --> 34:50.254
-Hey.
-No, hey. Hey! Ahh!

34:53.508 --> 34:54.717
Looks worse than it is.

35:01.599 --> 35:03.267
Where did you learn to do this?

35:03.351 --> 35:04.352
Max.

35:04.936 --> 35:07.939
First clean, then disinfect, then bandage.

35:11.359 --> 35:14.070
-Stop moving.
-Yeah, well, it stings. It stings!

35:14.153 --> 35:15.905
That means it's working.

35:16.864 --> 35:19.117
You're more like me
than I'd like to admit.

35:19.200 --> 35:21.786
What, a stubborn punk-ass?

35:21.869 --> 35:23.329
You heard that?

35:24.288 --> 35:25.456
You talk loud.

35:28.292 --> 35:30.628
Yeah, I guess I am a stubborn punk-ass.

35:31.963 --> 35:33.297
Or at least I was.

35:33.923 --> 35:36.175
I never listened to my pops either.

35:36.759 --> 35:38.886
Always thought I knew best.

35:38.970 --> 35:40.179
Pissed him right off.

35:42.306 --> 35:45.309
I remember one day it got so heated,
he took me to the recruitment office.

35:45.393 --> 35:47.228
He made me enlist right there.

35:47.311 --> 35:51.190
He thought the Army would do me some good.
Give me some structure, discipline.

35:53.234 --> 35:56.320
The thing was,
I thought I was smarter than the officers.

35:57.530 --> 35:58.489
Were you?

35:58.573 --> 35:59.824
Sometimes.

36:00.449 --> 36:03.327
But mostly, no, I was just dumb.

36:03.995 --> 36:04.996
Naive.

36:05.705 --> 36:08.416
I used to trust my gut and my instinct.

36:09.208 --> 36:11.586
Never… Like you.

36:13.379 --> 36:16.924
Did a lot of crazy things in that war.
Reckless things.

36:17.508 --> 36:19.177
You might call them brave,

36:19.677 --> 36:22.763
but there's a fine line
between bravery and stupidity.

36:23.890 --> 36:25.850
Saw a lot of brave men die in that war.

36:26.934 --> 36:28.311
Friends of mine.

36:29.854 --> 36:31.230
My daughter…

36:32.023 --> 36:33.357
Sara.

36:33.983 --> 36:35.526
She was brave.

36:43.951 --> 36:45.620
Bravest person I ever knew.

36:47.079 --> 36:51.250
She stared death in the face.
She never got scared. She never wavered.

36:52.210 --> 36:53.711
Fought her heart out.

36:54.337 --> 36:56.839
The doctors said
they never saw anything like it.

36:58.341 --> 37:00.676
They thought she was gonna make it too.

37:16.609 --> 37:19.695
So, that's why you don't want me in here?

37:21.405 --> 37:24.075
Because you think Vecna will win,

37:24.158 --> 37:25.243
and I will die?

37:25.326 --> 37:26.327
I don't think…

37:27.453 --> 37:29.288
I don't think anything. I've just…

37:32.124 --> 37:34.669
Just been around long enough to know that…

37:37.046 --> 37:39.382
you can't count on anything in this life.

37:45.429 --> 37:46.847
I don't want to lose you.

37:50.559 --> 37:51.477
I won't.

37:53.938 --> 37:55.815
Which is why whatever happens
from here on out,

37:55.898 --> 37:57.650
wherever this blood leads,

37:57.733 --> 37:59.652
I need you to do what I say.

38:00.236 --> 38:03.281
So don't be a stubborn punk-ass like you?

38:03.864 --> 38:06.158
Yeah, don't be a stubborn punk-ass.

38:18.879 --> 38:20.006
Hey, hey, hey!

38:21.090 --> 38:22.091
I lead.

38:40.401 --> 38:44.071
So sorry to disturb you, Doctor,
but it's the Wheeler children.

38:45.406 --> 38:46.324
What about them?

38:46.407 --> 38:48.701
They say they need to speak to you.
They say it's--

38:48.784 --> 38:49.785
An emergency!

38:49.869 --> 38:50.995
What kind of emergency?

38:51.078 --> 38:53.456
Our… Our sister,
she's missing, as you know.

38:53.539 --> 38:55.333
I understand. And I'm very sorry.

38:55.416 --> 38:57.376
Well, we think our mom has something.

38:57.460 --> 38:58.669
Or knows something.

38:58.753 --> 39:00.504
About our sister,
about finding our sister.

39:00.588 --> 39:02.840
And I wish I could get you in to see her.

39:02.923 --> 39:06.927
But your mother's recovering from surgery.
Her system is still in shock.

39:07.011 --> 39:10.389
And beyond that,
her larynx is extremely damaged.

39:10.473 --> 39:13.351
She wouldn't be able to talk,
even if she were awake.

39:13.434 --> 39:15.853
Right, but even so--

39:15.936 --> 39:17.146
Listen to me.

39:17.813 --> 39:20.775
Finding your mother
when you did saved her life.

39:20.858 --> 39:22.109
Let's not risk it now.

39:23.319 --> 39:24.695
All right, sweetheart.

39:28.908 --> 39:29.909
What now?

39:33.537 --> 39:35.539
So we need to change sheets in 307.

39:35.623 --> 39:39.460
Rooms 202 and 203 are vacant.
And they need mopping.

39:39.543 --> 39:41.337
Denise needs help later…

39:41.420 --> 39:44.340
-What?
-Come on.

39:44.423 --> 39:46.175
-What are we doing?
-Ignoring doctor's orders.

39:46.258 --> 39:48.719
-He said it's too risky.
-When has that stopped us before?

39:50.888 --> 39:52.598
Besides, did you smell his breath?

39:52.681 --> 39:54.475
I don't trust doctors who smoke…

39:54.975 --> 39:56.435
or call me "sweetheart."

40:11.325 --> 40:15.121
Hey, man, I'm gonna turn on Irwin.
One more loop around the zone?

40:15.830 --> 40:17.957
Yeah. Go ahead.

40:23.003 --> 40:25.423
No, wait. Scratch that.

40:26.132 --> 40:27.258
I think I got something.

40:27.842 --> 40:29.135
-Seriously?
-Is it Hop?

40:29.218 --> 40:32.471
Yeah, I… I don't know.
I'm not getting a hit on the decoder,

40:32.555 --> 40:34.098
but I can hear something.

40:34.849 --> 40:36.725
Yeah, I definitely hear something.

40:46.235 --> 40:47.278
Is that him?

40:48.320 --> 40:49.321
Yo, dude!

40:51.365 --> 40:52.908
Yeah, uh, we're not sure.

40:54.952 --> 40:57.621
-No, it's not Hop.
-What? Then what the hell is it?

40:57.705 --> 40:59.874
I don't know.
It could be a million things.

40:59.957 --> 41:03.669
Military broadcast, TV channel,
any EMI within our frequency zone.

41:03.752 --> 41:06.088
I do know it's not Hop's telemetry tag,

41:06.172 --> 41:09.425
because if it was,
it would show up on the decoder.

41:09.508 --> 41:11.802
So… search continues.

41:15.222 --> 41:18.517
Hey, Mom, um, disregard.
It's a false alarm.

41:19.727 --> 41:22.062
Jonathan, is your receiver
in any way connected

41:22.146 --> 41:23.814
to the flux capacitor?

41:25.524 --> 41:28.903
Uh, sorry, Mom.
Can, uh… Can you repeat that?

41:28.986 --> 41:30.279
The flux capacitor.

41:30.362 --> 41:31.697
Robin said it was down,

41:31.780 --> 41:33.741
but she and Will are working on it.

41:33.824 --> 41:36.076
I wanted to make sure
it wasn't messing with your connection.

41:38.120 --> 41:39.121
Hello?

41:41.499 --> 41:42.500
Hello?

41:58.891 --> 42:02.144
You know, we can still turn back
if you want.

42:02.853 --> 42:05.981
I'm more scared of my mom at this point,
to be honest.

42:06.065 --> 42:07.233
Fair.

42:17.159 --> 42:18.994
Is this where it happened?

42:21.497 --> 42:22.957
Where you had your vision?

42:25.251 --> 42:27.878
Yeah. Right here.

42:30.381 --> 42:33.092
Are you… feeling anything?

42:34.593 --> 42:35.594
No.

42:38.180 --> 42:39.181
What…

42:42.017 --> 42:44.395
So, what are we doing now, exactly?

42:44.478 --> 42:48.524
If your theory's right,
and my receiver is proximity-based,

42:48.607 --> 42:51.819
I need to get close to the Demo
to tap into the hive mind.

42:51.902 --> 42:55.656
And maybe, earlier,
when the Demo was passing by,

42:55.739 --> 42:58.075
it was headed for its monster lair.

42:58.158 --> 42:59.785
Right. Monster lair.

42:59.868 --> 43:02.329
We're already here.
Might as well push our luck.

43:10.170 --> 43:13.507
I've been meaning to ask you,
were you at the hospital yesterday?

43:13.591 --> 43:14.633
The hospital?

43:15.134 --> 43:16.677
No. No, no, no.

43:16.760 --> 43:21.307
Weird. I could have sworn
I saw you there, but…

43:21.890 --> 43:23.392
Vickie, she's a candy striper…

43:23.475 --> 43:24.810
-Oh yeah.
-She's my friend.

43:24.893 --> 43:27.438
We're friends. Good friends. But, uh…

43:28.230 --> 43:31.650
The thing is, some people
might not understand our friendship.

43:32.276 --> 43:36.113
Basically, what I'm trying to say is
if you were there and did see something,

43:36.196 --> 43:39.533
it might just be better if,
uh, nobody knew,

43:40.034 --> 43:41.368
if it stayed between us.

43:41.452 --> 43:42.703
I didn't see anything.

43:42.786 --> 43:46.290
Sorry. It's just
I tend to be off-topic when I'm nervous,

43:46.373 --> 43:48.959
and you said that thing
about monster lair, and I thought,

43:49.043 --> 43:52.087
"What if your mom was right,
and you get kidnapped by Vecna, and…"

43:52.171 --> 43:53.380
Holy shit.

43:54.089 --> 43:56.216
What… Where are you going?

43:56.300 --> 43:59.678
It's a mandala. Did you do this,
Mrs. Harris's class, fifth grade?

43:59.762 --> 44:03.307
So cool. Though, come to think of it,
it's not even really a mandala.

44:03.390 --> 44:06.352
I mean, it's just a spiral.
Mandalas are usually concentric circles

44:06.435 --> 44:08.437
but it's the thought that counts.

44:08.520 --> 44:10.022
Speaking of the thought that counts,

44:10.105 --> 44:14.777
is it a mandala,
or a mandah-la, or a man-dala?

44:17.863 --> 44:19.823
-I heard laughter.
-What?

44:20.908 --> 44:22.034
In my vision.

44:22.785 --> 44:25.245
Kids laughing, playing.

44:28.916 --> 44:32.127
What does that have to do
with a monster lair? Will!

44:49.978 --> 44:51.772
That's not a Demogorgon.

44:52.898 --> 44:54.274
Stay close to me.

45:04.827 --> 45:05.703
Hop?

45:09.832 --> 45:10.958
Jesus Christ.

45:14.461 --> 45:15.546
What is it?

45:38.986 --> 45:40.404
Holly was here.

45:43.699 --> 45:44.825
Right here.

45:48.287 --> 45:50.914
Maybe that's why
I can't find her in my mind.

45:52.833 --> 45:54.168
It took her…

45:56.170 --> 45:57.337
through the wall.

46:36.585 --> 46:37.836
Incoming, incoming.

46:39.296 --> 46:40.714
-Limp or something.
-What?

46:40.798 --> 46:41.757
Limp!

46:43.425 --> 46:44.802
…to New England?

46:44.885 --> 46:46.720
Oh, it is amazing.

46:46.804 --> 46:47.971
Don't look back.

46:48.847 --> 46:51.558
-What kind of limp is that?
-It's a limp, a regular limp.

46:51.642 --> 46:52.476
Whoa.

47:10.202 --> 47:11.411
Hi, Mom.

47:12.788 --> 47:15.374
Mom, can you hear us, Mom?

47:18.919 --> 47:20.087
Mom?

47:21.129 --> 47:22.256
Can you hear me?

47:24.591 --> 47:25.592
Mom.

47:31.056 --> 47:31.932
Hi.

47:32.724 --> 47:34.226
Hi there.

47:34.309 --> 47:35.769
Hi, Mom.

47:35.853 --> 47:37.271
Hey, Mom.

47:38.814 --> 47:40.232
Don't try to talk.

47:40.315 --> 47:43.277
It's your throat. It's gonna be okay.
It needs time to heal.

47:43.360 --> 47:44.361
Yeah.

47:45.320 --> 47:49.116
But could you… could you maybe write?

47:50.659 --> 47:53.245
Yeah? Okay.

47:53.328 --> 47:54.329
Okay.

48:12.556 --> 48:13.515
"Holly?"

48:14.850 --> 48:16.143
Yeah, that's, um…

48:16.935 --> 48:18.729
That is why we're here, Mom.

48:19.605 --> 48:20.564
Holly's…

48:23.901 --> 48:24.776
She's missing.

48:27.779 --> 48:29.615
Hey, we're gonna get her back.

48:29.698 --> 48:31.033
We just need your help.

48:31.116 --> 48:33.619
We think there's someone
that knows where Holly is,

48:33.702 --> 48:35.829
who knows why she was taken
and where she is.

48:35.913 --> 48:37.831
We just don't know where he is.

48:37.915 --> 48:40.459
And so, we're hoping that you might.

48:49.426 --> 48:50.385
"Who?"

48:50.969 --> 48:51.970
Um…

48:53.263 --> 48:58.268
We don't know his name, but Holly, she…

49:00.687 --> 49:02.773
she calls him Mr. Whatsit.

49:16.912 --> 49:17.829
Come on.

49:18.872 --> 49:20.999
I don't understand.
What exactly are we doing here?

49:21.083 --> 49:23.585
We're looking for this.

49:27.130 --> 49:30.884
"Teacher saw talking to W."

49:30.968 --> 49:32.719
"W" as in "Whatsit"?

49:35.389 --> 49:36.223
"Nobody…"

49:39.267 --> 49:40.143
"…there."

49:41.019 --> 49:43.230
In my vision earlier,
the sky was spinning.

49:44.481 --> 49:46.692
So, I think I was here,

49:46.775 --> 49:49.903
right here on this merry-go-round
during Ms. Harris's recess.

49:51.071 --> 49:52.239
Blast off!

49:52.322 --> 49:53.865
Derek, stop!

49:54.408 --> 49:56.368
Stop, Derek! Get off! Go away!

49:57.244 --> 50:00.205
I don't understand. I thought you were
seeing through the Demogorgon.

50:00.288 --> 50:01.123
I know. So did I.

50:01.206 --> 50:03.750
But you said yourself
Vecna controls the hive mind,

50:03.834 --> 50:07.337
which means he's a part of it too.
So, when he searches for his victims…

50:07.421 --> 50:09.881
-He invades their minds.
-He sees what they see.

50:09.965 --> 50:13.677
Did Holly ever describe
Mr. Whatsit to you?

50:13.760 --> 50:18.348
Like, maybe what he's wearing
or anything like that?

50:19.307 --> 50:22.269
Holly, time for breakfast.

50:24.312 --> 50:25.188
"Pocket watch."

50:26.606 --> 50:28.734
"Tall. Vest."

50:29.443 --> 50:31.361
Okay, he wears a vest.

50:31.445 --> 50:35.365
Uh, he's gentle and kind.

50:35.449 --> 50:40.787
So, what if I was seeing
through the eyes of Vecna's next victim,

50:40.871 --> 50:44.416
this victim he's stalking,
which means I was seeing through--

50:44.499 --> 50:45.584
Holly's eyes.

50:46.460 --> 50:48.170
But if that's true, it would mean…

50:48.253 --> 50:49.296
I was him.

50:50.505 --> 50:51.506
I was Vecna.

50:54.509 --> 50:57.304
Did Holly ever say if he has a first name?

51:02.851 --> 51:04.227
Are the others here yet?

51:05.937 --> 51:06.897
No, not yet.

51:08.607 --> 51:12.778
You will save them, too, won't you?
Save them from the monsters?

51:13.653 --> 51:18.658
Yes, Holly. Don't you worry.
I'm going to save your friends.

51:22.037 --> 51:23.205
Every last one of them.

51:28.460 --> 51:29.628
And my family?

51:30.921 --> 51:32.380
Are they coming too?

51:40.722 --> 51:42.015
Your friends first.

51:42.933 --> 51:45.477
Then after, I'll save your family too,
of course.

51:47.187 --> 51:49.022
I have room for everyone here.

52:12.337 --> 52:14.339
Mr. Sandman

52:14.840 --> 52:16.466
Bring me a dream

52:17.342 --> 52:21.388
Make him the cutest
That I've ever seen

52:21.471 --> 52:26.017
Give him two lips
Like roses and clover

52:26.101 --> 52:29.771
Then tell him that
His lonesome nights are over

52:29.855 --> 52:31.231
Sandman

52:32.357 --> 52:34.776
I'm so alone

52:34.860 --> 52:37.988
Don't have nobody to call my own

52:38.864 --> 52:42.576
Please turn on your magic beam

52:42.659 --> 52:46.121
Mr. Sandman, bring me a dream

53:04.222 --> 53:09.227
Mr. Sandman, bring me a dream

53:09.311 --> 53:13.315
Make him the cutest
That I've ever seen

53:13.398 --> 53:17.319
Give him the word that I'm not a rover

53:17.402 --> 53:21.198
Then tell him that
His lonesome nights are over

53:21.281 --> 53:25.410
Sandman, I'm so alone

53:25.493 --> 53:29.497
Don't have nobody to call my own

53:29.581 --> 53:32.500
Please turn on your magic beam

53:32.584 --> 53:36.713
Ah, Mr. Sandman, bring me a dream

53:50.018 --> 53:51.686
Mr. Sandman

53:51.770 --> 53:52.812
Yes?

53:52.896 --> 53:54.397
Bring us a dream

53:54.481 --> 53:58.693
Give him a pair of eyes
With a come-hither gleam

53:58.777 --> 54:03.865
Give him a lonely heart like Pagliacci

54:03.949 --> 54:07.744
And lots of wavy hair like Liberace

54:08.620 --> 54:12.624
-Mr. Sandman, someone to hold
-Someone to hold

54:12.707 --> 54:16.086
Would be so peachy
Before we're too old

54:16.169 --> 54:20.423
So please turn on your magic beam

54:20.507 --> 54:24.386
Mr. Sandman, bring me a dream

54:29.182 --> 54:31.810
Mr. Sandman, bring us

54:31.893 --> 54:33.603
Please, please, please

54:33.687 --> 54:36.231
Mr. Sandman

54:36.314 --> 57:52.699
Bring us a dream
